    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Up for sale is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black, representing a pinnacle of atmospheric engine development. This example is powered by the S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to produce 333 hp with an 8,000 RPM redline. The power is managed by a traditional 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and sent to the rear wheels via a torque-sensing M Differential Lock. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed: the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates to prevent floor failure, and the VANOS system has been overhauled with upgraded seals. The suspension geometry remains precise, featuring refreshed control arm bushings and a set of Bilstein B6 dampers for improved rebound characteristics. While the exterior shows minor road-wear consistent with its age, the mechanical integrity is superlative, offering the tactile steering feedback and high-revving linear power delivery this chassis is legendary for.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 48
    },
    {
